Package cz.cvut.fel.pjv.model.utils

Class SimulationState

java.lang.Object
cz.cvut.fel.pjv.model.utils.SimulationState
public class SimulationState extends Object
Manages the state of the simulation, including the list of movers and the sun.

Uses ArrayList to store Mover objects and provides methods to create default states and custom states with or without an attractor.

    • createDefaultState

      public void createDefaultState()
      Creates a default simulation state with 100 movers and a sun.

      Uses Point2DExt.random2D() and Point2DExt.rotate(Point2D, double) for position and velocity calculations.

    • createNwithoutAtractor

      public void createNwithoutAtractor(int n)
      Creates a simulation state with the specified number of movers without an attractor.

      Uses Point2DExt.random2D() and Point2DExt.rotate(Point2D, double) for position and velocity calculations.

      Parameters:
      n - the number of Mover movers to create.

    • createNwithAtractor

      public void createNwithAtractor(int n, Mover sun)
      Creates a simulation state with the specified number of movers and an attractor (sun).

      Uses Point2DExt.random2D() and Point2DExt.rotate(Point2D, double) for position and velocity calculations.

      Parameters:
      n - the number of Mover movers to create.
      sun - the sun Mover object to act as an attractor.
